OL,3,CThe reality of having a loved one with
OL,4,Cdementia - and fears for Wales' future
OL,6,F"My fear is that one day I'm going to
OL,7,Fgo and see her - and she's not going
OL,8,Fto know who I am," she said.
OL,10,FGloria was always up for a laugh and a
OL,11,F"party animal" in her younger years,
OL,12,Fregularly socialising and enjoying
OL,13,Fherself with friends and family.
OL,15,FNatalie said: "It's sad because I
OL,16,Fnever expected my mum to be like this.
OL,17,FShe hasn't been right for about nine
OL,18,Fyears, but the last three were the
OL,19,Fworst because she kept coming to my
OL,20,Fplace of work saying 'I've lost this,
OL,21,FI've lost that.'
