OL,3,CThe reality of having a loved one with
OL,4,Cdementia - and fears for Wales' future
OL,6,F"Every day I was going up there to
OL,7,Fcheck she was okay, but even carers
OL,8,Fwould go in and say 'Come on, Glo, get
OL,9,Fout of bed. Come and have a shower'
OL,10,Fbut she'd say 'no thank you'. She
OL,11,Fdidn't wash or anything. And that's
OL,12,Fnot her at all - she was the cleanest
OL,13,Fperson on the planet.
OL,15,F"I remember when I was a kid, she'd be
OL,16,Fout the front door scrubbing the step
OL,17,Flike everybody else used to do."
