OL,3,CThe reality of having a loved one with
OL,4,Cdementia - and fears for Wales' future
OL,6,F"She went in on respite, because I
OL,7,Fknew she was struggling, but I had a
OL,8,Fphone call saying, 'she doesn't want
OL,9,Fto go home'.
OL,11,F"I thought 'yes!' It's company for
OL,12,Fher, she loved it. There's somebody
OL,13,Fthere if she needs them - because she
OL,14,Fwas just left to their own devices in
OL,15,Fa little flat. In this home she's got
OL,16,Fall her friends.
OL,18,F"But she has to pay for everything she
OL,19,Fgets. It's very tough, so she sold her
OL,20,Fhouse to pay for what she's getting
OL,21,Fnow."
